        "ordinal": 7
      },
      "body_sha256": "a95eacb2ddd12356d1c99b0f2c95404af90269db0aeb46e6cf5c79162b3a3a3c",
      "body_chars": 231,
      "body_excerpt": "In the movie The Matrix one of the characters (Neo) uses a computer to very rapidly upload martial arts skills into his mind. As he opens hi"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-8",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 9",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 8
      },
      "body_sha256": "c5fd58a379aae23398effe874644b4483d41ea14ff2c2f9340ae5ebb9a254e4a",
      "body_chars": 84,
      "body_excerpt": "We've made no attempt at all to scale this out. It's interesting to ponder doing so."
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-9",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 10",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 9
      },
      "body_sha256": "fa6dc68cbb2c52a477d9586b87a2a959eeb7f4f62f04ed94233ee47beeb4dbd1",
      "body_chars": 547,
      "body_excerpt": "In more detail: there were 16 users in the group that did the reviews, per usual, and 25 users in the group where reviews were delayed. The "
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-10",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 11",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 10
      },
      "body_sha256": "00c00b5c081f14a108dea89dedee776b65cb8e061f762246bdd2fc0d0294f4d2",
      "body_chars": 191,
      "body_excerpt": "Strictly speaking, Quizlet's basic product doesn't use spaced repetition. There is, however, a paid version using spaced repetition, and it'"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-11",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 12",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 11
      },
      "body_sha256": "aa4c18e9fa1406a267ac264094864eecdf426e6076eb35777599fc79965fbbf3",
      "body_chars": 148,
      "body_excerpt": "They are, however, widely used within some interesting niche audiences. For instance, there is a thriving population of medical students usi"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-12",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 13",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 12
      },
      "body_sha256": "d1bf2e7b7b8a4e3508ef32df7f82d6cf6776a795bd33dd23aba6739a37785d78",
      "body_chars": 214,
      "body_excerpt": "More generally, Wozniak is, along with Sebastian Leitner, the principal pioneer of spaced-repetition memory systems. Much of Wozniak's think"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-13",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 14",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
