        "ordinal": 17
      },
      "body_sha256": "6706d1ee2ef3d86c897f5c55a00d09085cf70fba88885ff598d519455cc7d7bb",
      "body_chars": 124,
      "body_excerpt": "An enjoyable extended introduction to such techniques may be found in Joshua Foer's book \u201cMoonwalking with Einstein\u201d (2012)."
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-18",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 19",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 18
      },
      "body_sha256": "6bccfa2c765a205b1f2d441dfb846d976dd915c4069d95a12f753a685a66e92f",
      "body_chars": 408,
      "body_excerpt": "A small minority of the population does not possess a mind's eye, and so cannot mentally visualize. This condition is known as aphantasia. O"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-19",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 20",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 19
      },
      "body_sha256": "a18fe4784d6af5bfd6024c84a62c150d86b354e1c2db648adf4b6f55f77fc31b",
      "body_chars": 139,
      "body_excerpt": "See here and here for more on learning new fields using Anki. The last four paragraphs are adapted from Augmenting Long-term Memory (2018)."
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-20",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 21",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 20
      },
      "body_sha256": "13cdaf5fe67212e096717d5f30deb0554e1bbe69820a78d779381d2deb761638",
      "body_chars": 148,
      "body_excerpt": "The last two paragraphs are adapted from our forthcoming mnemonic essay: Andy Matuschak and Michael Nielsen, How quantum teleportation works"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-21",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 22",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 21
      },
      "body_sha256": "518bbf512437315f1bd08c6f00df82ea391970c9999e1f60f0f941d17bc18912",
      "body_chars": 220,
      "body_excerpt": "See, e.g., William G. Chase and Herbert A. Simon, Perception in Chess (1973). Some fascinating earlier work in a related vein was done by Ad"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-22",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 23",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 22
      },
      "body_sha256": "a3a2637e939bb96f5a9548fe929387ebf0e0b962c19b70211de0dc71c3641c8c",
      "body_chars": 501,
      "body_excerpt": "We've met many mathematicians and physicists who say that one reason they went into mathematics or physics is because they hated the rote me"
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-23",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 24",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 23
      },
      "body_sha256": "955a6fd9e057e633e4faa9e90d8b5014935f5504db2490525bdf48e62e541320",
      "body_chars": 250,
      "body_excerpt": "The same phenomenon occurs in the conventional grade-school algorithms for multiplication and division. One of us has spun a short piece of "
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-24",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 25",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 24
      },
      "body_sha256": "645f4d2cefc90f1758c2d0d0e531d5df6e9129a8ae025bba3be8de550cbd8a07",
      "body_chars": 267,
      "body_excerpt": "Of course, a designer who spoke to an expert on, say, Babylonian mathematics, might well have come across some of these ideas. We'll ignore "
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-25",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 26",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
      "source_ref": {
        "format": "html",
        "fragment_idx": 0,
        "element": "span.marginnote",
        "ordinal": 25
      },
      "body_sha256": "42b48ee4aa5cdfce30832e50cbad054874fa1eb5697c0e0837991dbccf47b682",
      "body_chars": 64,
      "body_excerpt": "These images excerpted from Astronomy: Exploring Time and Space."
    },
    {
      "gold_key": "t:numinous-ttft:margin-note-26",
      "kind": "margin_note",
      "label": "Margin note 27",
      "confidence": "strong",
      "extraction_method": "html_margin_note",
